<$fill $name="body">

! What it does

By default the search input filters the ''current stage's'' visible rows only and matches against each row's `name` and `hint` slots. Three pill strips widen this on independent axes:

* ''Reach'' (teal) — WHERE in the cascade tree to search. Default: local (current stage only).
* ''Meta'' (violet) — WHICH cascade-item author meta keys the matcher reads (the row's display-time slots: `name` / `hint`, plus any author-defined keys). Default: per-row `ca-search-fields`, falling back to global default `name hint`.
* ''Field'' (amber) — WHICH literal tiddler fields the matcher reads on the row's backing tiddler (`text` / `caption` / `tags` / author-defined). Default: not consulted unless a Field pill is pushed.

All three strips use the same push / remove / DEL / navigate grammar as the existing Filter and Visibility strips. Strips appear only when at least one pill is pushed — unless you toggle Settings → ''Pin all pill rows'' (0.0.87+), which keeps every strip visible as a dev / discoverability aid.

! Reach strip — WHERE to search

|!Pill |!Leader |!Effect |
|🔍 Here |`d` |Walk every reachable drill under the currently-visible stage. |
|🌐 Everywhere |`g` |Walk every reachable drill under the active view's root. The drill stack stays put — the pill widens the search frontier, it doesn't move you. |

The two Reach pills are ''mutually exclusive'' — pushing one evicts the other. Only one scope is ever active. DEL on the focused pill removes it (returning to local search).

When a Reach pill is active, results carry a breadcrumb prefix (`Kinds → Task → fields  priority: enum`) naming the drill chain from the search anchor to the matched row.

! Meta strip — WHICH cascade-item author meta keys

Pills tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/search-meta`''. Each declares a `ca-meta-key` naming the cascade-item property the matcher reads.

|!Pill |!`ca-meta-key` |!Source |!Visible inline? |
|🏷 Name |`name` |`ca-name` on entries; synthesised from `caption` → path-segment → title on tiddler-backed rows |Yes — the row's title. Inline match highlight. |
|💡 Hint |`hint` |`ca-hint` on entries (empty on tiddler-backed rows without an explicit ca-hint) |Yes — the row's subtitle. Inline match highlight. |

Multiple Meta pills can coexist. When any are active, the matcher reads the UNION of those slots, ignoring per-row `ca-search-fields` and the global default. No Meta pills active → matcher uses each row's `ca-search-fields` declaration, falling back to the global default at ''`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/search-fields-default`'' (ships `name hint`).

! Field strip — WHICH literal tiddler fields

Pills tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/search-field`''. Each declares a `ca-tiddler-field` naming the tiddler field the matcher reads on the row's backing tiddler.

|!Pill |!`ca-tiddler-field` |!Source |
|📄 Text |`text` |The backing tiddler's `text` field — the wikitext / content body. |

Multiple Field pills can coexist; the matcher unions them. Synthetic rows (no backing tiddler) silently skip every Field pill. No Field pills active → the matcher skips the tiddler-field channel entirely (default keeps search fast).

''Leader `a`'' pushes all six shipped search pills at once (five Meta + one Field) — equivalent to "match anywhere".

! Authoring custom Meta pills

Ship a tiddler tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/search-meta`'' that names a cascade-item property the matcher should consult. Example — a `caption` pill for the row's display name (only useful if you populate `item.caption` somewhere; usually you'd ship a Field pill instead):

```
title: $:/config/myplugin/search-meta/displayname
tags: $:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/search-meta
ca-meta-key: displayname
ca-chip: 🪧 Display name
ca-hint: Match against the row's displayname slot.
ca-order: 160
```

! Authoring custom Field pills

Ship a tiddler tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/search-field`'' that names a tiddler field the matcher should read on each row's backing tiddler. Example — a `caption` pill for the tiddler's caption field:

```
title: $:/config/myplugin/search-field/caption
tags: $:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/search-field
ca-tiddler-field: caption
ca-chip: 🪧 Caption
ca-hint: Match against the tiddler's caption field.
ca-order: 110
```

Array-typed fields (`tags`, list-fields) are flattened to space-separated strings before substring matching, so a Field pill on `tags` matches `urgen` against `tags: work urgent`.

! Multi-match visualization

When a row matches in multiple slots (e.g. Name AND Description, or Description AND Text), each match contributes:

* Inline highlight on the visible name / hint slot (whichever matched).
* One snippet line per non-displayed match (`text`, or any author-defined key the matcher consulted), shown beneath the row with the matched pill's chip label + 24 chars of context before + the matched substring (highlighted) + 40 chars after.

So a single row can carry inline highlight AND multiple snippets — the user sees every reason the row is in the result list. The snippet caption reads the pill's chip ("📝 Description") rather than the bare slot name, so labels stay readable.

! Picking a deep result — three gestures

When a Reach pill is active, results carry a `_path` array (the drill chain from the anchor). Picking a result replays the path so the cascade lands at the row's natural parent. Three gestures distinguish what happens next:

|!Gesture |!Effect |
|''Enter'' |Replay path + execute (fire leaves, drill into drills). |
|''Right-arrow'' |Replay path + drill (no-op on plain leaves). |
|''Space'' |''Pin only'' — replay path, select the row at its natural stage, but do NOT fire / edit / open the action menu. Safe inspection gesture for destructive matches. |

Any `<<parent-picked>>` / `<<stage-N-picked>>` context the row's actions depend on resolves the same way as a manual drill.

! Authoring searchable text on cascade items

The shipped Meta pills read `name` and `hint` only. To make additional searchable content available on a row, author a custom Meta pill (see above) that names whichever cascade-item property you want exposed, and stamp that property onto items in your row-builder. Two opt-out / per-row controls remain on the protocol:

```
ca-search-fields: name hint   (per-row override of the searched meta keys)
ca-search-skip: yes           (exclude from deep walk)
```

''`ca-search-skip: yes`'' opts a row out of deep search results AND prevents its subtree from being descended. Useful for `+ Add new` input prompts whose name only makes sense in their immediate context. Default auto-skip applies to `text`, `number`, `date`, `toggle`, and `confirm` row kinds.

! Caps

The walk is bounded — no walk is ever unbounded — by three hard caps (config tiddler defaults):

|!Config |!Default |!What it does |
|`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/deep-search-max-depth` |4 |Maximum drill depth from the search anchor |
|`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/deep-search-max-nodes` |800 |Total items visited before the walk aborts |
|`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/deep-search-max-ms` |80 |Wall-clock time per keystroke before the walk aborts |

When any cap fires, the result list ends with a ''truncation hint row'' so you know to refine the query.

! Sending the messages programmatically

A toolbar button, sidebar item, or any external wikitext can push pills via the same widget messages the leaders use:

```
<$action-sendmessage $message="rimir-cascade-palette-add-reach"
  reach="$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/reach/here"/>

<$action-sendmessage $message="rimir-cascade-palette-add-meta"
  meta="$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/search-meta/name"/>

<$action-sendmessage $message="rimir-cascade-palette-add-field"
  field="$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/search-field/text"/>
```

`rimir-cascade-palette-reset-reach` / `-reset-meta` / `-reset-fields` clear the respective strips.

! Migration from 0.0.87 and earlier

The old single Search-in strip is gone. Pills used to be tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/search-field`'' (or the pre-0.0.84 legacy ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/field`'') with a single `ca-field-name` field. Both schemas are no longer honoured.

* Pills that read a cascade-item author meta key (anything except `text`) move to the Meta strip — retag to ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/search-meta`'' and rename `ca-field-name` → `ca-meta-key`.
* Pills that read a literal tiddler field (only `text` among the shipped ones) stay on the Field strip — keep the tag, rename `ca-field-name` → `ca-tiddler-field`.
* `ca-field-chip` / `ca-field-hint` / `ca-field-help` rename to `ca-chip` / `ca-hint` / `ca-help` in both strips.
* The leader `a` still pushes every shipped pill — but now via two messages (`add-meta` for each Meta pill, `add-field` for each Field pill).

The diagnostics drill ''Deprecations'' (under Configurations) lists any tiddlers still on the legacy schema.

! Limitations (MVP)

* Action menus are not walked. Search lists the entity rows themselves; drilling into an action menu is a separate gesture.
* No per-keystroke memo cache yet — each keystroke recomputes the walk. Caps keep this fast on real-world trees.
* Result ranking is BFS-natural (shallower matches first; same-depth keeps cascade's sort). Exact-match boost and other ranking are on the roadmap.
* Pills don't persist across sessions or get saved into Presets yet — they're session-local. Preset integration is on the roadmap.
* No ''+ Add Meta / + Add Field'' picker pill yet (à la Presets' `+` save pill) — pills are pushed only via leaders or external messages for now.

